data.title: A dollar goes a long way in this cafe!
data.text: Decided to stop by this place. It's a well known establishment that caters to the city employees around the corner. Its serves up breakfast and lunch at very reasonable prices. Breakfast starts at $3.25 for your standard egg breakfast plate and lunch run about 6 bucks a plate. The food is good, the plates are served well and at these prices, you really cant go wrong.

data.title: If you are near Downtown Brownsville, this is the place for Breakfast and Lunch.
data.text:
This is a true hidden gem in the restaurant-filled streets of Brownsville.

This is a family-run Mexican place which consistently goes above and beyond with their food. Everything I have tried has been freshly prepared, tasty, and best of all...not the usual Tex-Mex with lots of grease dripping everywhere.

I have had their breakfast tacos, lunch plates, and soup, and I have yet to be disappointed in the food or the service. The owner or one of his family members will wait on you, and they are very friendly and accommodating. The food comes out fast. Plus, they will deliver to nearby places. 

I have eaten Mexican food all over Texas, the US, and Mexico, and this is right up there with some of the best IMO, and I suggest giving them a try.
